1
00:00:11,233 --> 00:00:14,467
- Whatever she told you...
- I told them the truth, Mommy.

2
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:16,467
That you're not hurting me.

3
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:19,033
I know who the culprit is.

4
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:20,267
She shouldn't treat her mother

5
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:22,300
as a family
if she's hurting her.

6
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:25,033
Olive is still Mookie's mother.

7
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:26,267
Not you.

8
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:31,600
Can you drop the charges
against Emma?

9
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:33,267
I already gave you my word.

10
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:35,733
Of course, I will keep it.

11
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:36,900
I've been feeling restless.

12
00:00:36,967 --> 00:00:39,667
Her mother might be doing
something to her again.

13
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:40,533
Here you go again.

14
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,300
You think about nothing
but Mookie.

15
00:00:42,367 --> 00:00:46,433
Do you want to know
if I did what you wanted?

16
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:48,700
I dropped the charges
against her.

17
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:53,333
I will do anything
and everything for you.

18
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:34,100
How are you, Flor?

19
00:01:34,167 --> 00:01:37,533
I'm still a slave to money.

20
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:43,967
I'm sorry I couldn't visit
you when you were in jail.

21
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,100
It's okay.

22
00:01:46,167 --> 00:01:48,033
I understand your situation.

23
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:49,267
Hold on.

24
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:50,233
I'll just buy some of that.

25
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,633
Mister, how much is tilapia?

26
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:53,800
P140, Ma'am.

27
00:01:53,867 --> 00:01:57,033
P140? Okay, please give me
a half kilo.

28
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,567
- And please remove the scales.
- Sure, Ma'am.

29
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:00,033
Thank you.

30
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:00,700
Okay.
Flor.

31
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:02,000
Yeah?

32
00:02:03,167 --> 00:02:05,267
How's Mookie?

33
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,433
She remains the same.

34
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,533
She remains where she is.

35
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:12,967
Flor, can I ask you a favor?

36
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:14,567
God, Emma.

37
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:16,533
I can sense that you're
going to ask me

38
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,633
for something dangerous.

39
00:02:19,567 --> 00:02:21,533
I want to talk to Mookie...

40
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:24,400
before I leave.

41
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:26,467
You're leaving?

42
00:02:26,533 --> 00:02:27,467
Where are you going?

43
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:30,433
We're going to move out.

44
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:32,133
Dan and I will go
to the province.

45
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,167
Thank you.

46
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:35,133
That's where he'll be assigned.

47
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,533
I want to talk to Mookie
before I go.

48
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:45,500
I can't promise,
but I'll see what I can do.

49
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:47,733
How much is that again?

50
00:02:47,833 --> 00:02:49,067
P140, Ma'am.

51
00:02:49,133 --> 00:02:50,533
It's so affordable.

52
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:51,400
I only got a half kilo, right?

53
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:52,700
Yes.

54
00:02:52,767 --> 00:02:53,467
Thank you, Ma'am.

55
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:54,633
Thank you, Mister.

56
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,100
I hope I can sell
all my merchandise.

57
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:56,733
Okay.

58
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,300
Someone's calling.

59
00:02:58,367 --> 00:03:00,667
It's Ma'am Olive!

60
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,200
I think she came from
a family of bats.

61
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:04,600
Her radar is so strong.

62
00:03:04,667 --> 00:03:06,200
I'll go ahead.

63
00:03:06,267 --> 00:03:07,067
Thank you, Mister.

64
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:08,500
Please see us again.

65
00:03:08,567 --> 00:03:09,433
Ma'am, yes.

66
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:31,067
You've been here for a while,
but your mind is on Mars.

67
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:34,733
I just remembered
something, Flor.

68
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:39,033
I bet you're thinking
about Emma.

69
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:47,033
That's what she cooked
for me when I got sick.

70
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,667
I just remembered it.

71
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:55,000
Do you want to see her?

72
00:03:57,233 --> 00:03:57,533
How?

73
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:06,333
Wait. Let's talk later.

74
00:04:09,133 --> 00:04:10,500
What are you talking about?

75
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,667
Nothing, Mom.

76
00:04:14,733 --> 00:04:17,667
I'm just asking her to
teach me how to cook.

77
00:04:19,733 --> 00:04:20,500
Flor?

78
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:21,633
Yes, Ma'am?

79
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,100
I need my suit.

80
00:04:23,167 --> 00:04:24,700
I need to go to the office.

81
00:04:24,767 --> 00:04:26,367
Okay, Ma'am.

82
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:28,033
I'll take care of it.

83
00:04:28,133 --> 00:04:32,167
Mookie, are you sure
you don't want me to stay here?

84
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:34,167
I can cancel my meeting.

85
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:35,533
Mommy, it's okay.

86
00:04:36,767 --> 00:04:38,167
I'll be fine here.

87
00:04:38,233 --> 00:04:40,133
I'm with Flor anyway.

88
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:43,067
Okay.

89
00:04:44,467 --> 00:04:45,300
My suit.

90
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:46,400
Yes, Ma'am.

91
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:47,300
- I need it now.
- I got it, Ma'am.
Yes.

92
00:04:49,733 --> 00:04:50,267
Mookie.

93
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,267
She's leaving.

94
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,433
I'll just get her suit.

95
00:04:57,067 --> 00:04:57,733
Go and eat.
Okay.

96
00:05:09,467 --> 00:05:10,467
Emma, come on and eat.

97
00:05:10,533 --> 00:05:12,400
I need to go back to work.

98
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,733
Your cell phone is ringing.

99
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,033
Someone's calling.

100
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:22,067
It's Flor.

101
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:26,233
Hello, Flor?

102
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:28,600
Emma, I have good news.

103
00:05:28,667 --> 00:05:30,667
Ma'am Olive is going to
leave at 1:00 o'clock.

104
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,267
Can I go?

105
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,000
I'll meet you
at the main gate.

106
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:36,267
Wait for me there.

107
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,200
Okay. Thank you, Flor.

108
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:42,700
Are you going to your
employer's house again?

109
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:47,400
I'll just talk to Mookie
while her mother is away.

110
00:05:47,467 --> 00:05:48,533
You're crazy!

111
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:52,633
What if Madam Olive catches you?

112
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:53,767
She'll send you to jail again!

113
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,567
She'll charge you
with trespassing.

114
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:56,467
You'll end up
in prison again.

115
00:05:57,467 --> 00:05:59,033
Your mom is right.

116
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:00,333
That's dangerous.

117
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:02,667
Use your brain.

118
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:06,000
Mom.

119
00:06:06,067 --> 00:06:09,200
You don't understand.

120
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:13,300
I just need to do this so
I can move on from Mookie.

121
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,100
Let me do this just this once.

122
00:06:18,067 --> 00:06:20,167
I'll forget Mookie after this.

123
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,567
Mommy Emma.

124
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:43,200
Mookie.

125
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:49,433
Mommy Emma.

126
00:07:03,733 --> 00:07:05,100
How are you, Mookie?

127
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:08,300
I'm doing well.

128
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,133
How about you?

129
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,100
I'm happy to see you again.

130
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:20,400
I've been praying to see
you even for a bit.

131
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:24,433
I'm happy that
you're back home.

132
00:07:25,267 --> 00:07:26,467
You know what?

133
00:07:28,633 --> 00:07:31,667
I didn't tell the
authorities the truth

134
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:39,233
so I could convince mommy to
drop the charges against you.

135
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:43,167
You asked your mom to let me go?

136
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:48,433
Is that why you didn't report
her to the authorities?

137
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:52,667
That's the only way
I could think of.

138
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:57,033
Mookie, you shouldn't
have done that.

139
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,467
It's okay, Mommy Emma.

140
00:08:00,233 --> 00:08:05,367
I wanted to do that
because I love you so much.

141
00:08:06,633 --> 00:08:08,167
I love you, too, Mookie.

142
00:08:09,167 --> 00:08:10,133
I love you so much.

143
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:15,600
I came here to thank you.

144
00:08:17,467 --> 00:08:19,067
And to tell you...

145
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,233
that no matter what happens,

146
00:08:23,167 --> 00:08:26,233
you will remain in my mind
and my heart.

147
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:33,567
But why are you sad?

148
00:08:36,633 --> 00:08:37,700
Don't you like that?

149
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:41,433
We'll be together more often.

150
00:08:42,667 --> 00:08:44,000
Don't worry.

151
00:08:44,067 --> 00:08:47,100
Because my mom will
never hurt me again.

152
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:51,333
We'll make many more memories.

153
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,233
Right?

154
00:08:57,533 --> 00:09:00,067
This is one of the hardest
things I will do.

155
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:04,967
If only everything you
want could happen, Mookie.

156
00:09:05,033 --> 00:09:06,200
Everything you said.

157
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:10,167
But...

158
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:13,333
I need to say goodbye.

159
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:28,333
You're leaving, Mommy Emma?

160
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:33,167
Where will you go?

161
00:09:34,133 --> 00:09:35,267
Why?

162
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:42,933
We want to try our
luck somewhere else.

163
00:09:44,067 --> 00:09:49,667
Uncle Dan asked his company
to transfer him to a province.

164
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:53,367
He wants a quiet life.

165
00:09:55,767 --> 00:09:58,500
But is that also what you want?

166
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:06,700
Of course, as his wife,

167
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:11,067
I need to be where
your Uncle Dan will be.

168
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:17,400
But what about me?

169
00:10:17,467 --> 00:10:20,100
How can I get better
without you?

170
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:25,167
Mookie, you can do it.

171
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:27,467
You're brave and
strong, aren't you?

172
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:33,000
Flor and Zayn are here.

173
00:10:33,067 --> 00:10:34,967
They will take care of you.

174
00:10:35,367 --> 00:10:39,667
Mommy Emma, I want to be
brave and strong with you.

175
00:10:40,567 --> 00:10:43,233
Please, don't leave.

176
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:45,467
We'll be together again.

177
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:48,067
We'll make many more
memories, right?

178
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:49,700
You told me that.

179
00:10:49,767 --> 00:10:53,733
We'll make more
memories together.

180
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:56,533
You won't leave me, right?

181
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,367
That's what you told me.

182
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:01,167
Sorry, dear.

183
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:08,233
Even if I want to be with
you longer, I must leave.

184
00:11:08,967 --> 00:11:13,667
Maybe you should just
forget about me.

185
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:18,367
Forget you?

186
00:11:19,433 --> 00:11:21,200
Why, Mommy Emma?

187
00:11:21,267 --> 00:11:24,600
Why? Don't you love me anymore?

188
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:27,133
Didn't you tell me you love me?

189
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,700
Why are you leaving me?

190
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:30,467
Why will you go away?

191
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:33,700
I can't understand.

192
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:37,300
Mookie, I love you.

193
00:11:37,367 --> 00:11:38,400
I love you so much.

194
00:11:38,467 --> 00:11:40,733
Why will you go away?

195
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,400
I'm doing this for you.

196
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:46,400
For your sake.

197
00:11:46,467 --> 00:11:51,600
Your mommy will keep hurting
you if I don't leave.

198
00:11:51,667 --> 00:11:54,133
She will give you a hard time.

199
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:57,100
And I don't want you to
suffer because of me.

200
00:11:57,167 --> 00:11:58,500
No.

201
00:11:58,567 --> 00:12:00,433
Mommy Emma, I don't want it.

202
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:03,167
I don't want you to leave.

203
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:04,533
Please.

204
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:07,067
We can find a lot
of other ways.

205
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:09,267
Please. I don't want
you to leave.

206
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:10,467
Please, Mom.

207
00:12:10,533 --> 00:12:12,667
This is so painful for me.

208
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:17,000
But this is the last time
we're going to see each other.

209
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:18,033
Mom.

210
00:12:18,733 --> 00:12:19,533
Mom.
- Please.
- Mookie...

211
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:22,733
goodbye.
Mom!

212
00:12:23,767 --> 00:12:25,200
Mom!

213
00:12:25,867 --> 00:12:29,967
Mom, you promised me
you wouldn't leave me.

214
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:33,100
Why are you leaving?

215
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:35,500
I don't want you to leave.

216
00:12:35,567 --> 00:12:38,000
Please!

217
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:39,500
Don't! Mom!

218
00:12:40,233 --> 00:12:40,967
Mom!

219
00:12:43,533 --> 00:12:44,633
Mom!

220
00:12:45,567 --> 00:12:46,967
Mom!

221
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:48,800
No!

222
00:12:48,867 --> 00:12:50,133
Flor!

223
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,200
Flor! I don't want to!

224
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:55,700
Don't let her leave.

225
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:58,800
I don't want her to leave!

226
00:12:58,867 --> 00:13:02,700
Flor, please, close the gate.

227
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,700
I don't want her to leave!

228
00:13:04,933 --> 00:13:07,433
Flor!

229
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:10,667
You said you wouldn't leave me!

230
00:13:12,533 --> 00:13:15,167
Why did you leave me?

231
00:13:25,467 --> 00:13:27,233
I told you so.

232
00:13:28,167 --> 00:13:29,433
This wouldn't happen to you

233
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:32,600
if you stayed out of that
child's life.

234
00:13:32,667 --> 00:13:34,433
Mom, please stop.

235
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:36,167
Emma's already crying.

236
00:13:37,433 --> 00:13:39,300
She cries as if she
lost a child.

237
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:40,533
Mom!

238
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,200
That's way out of line.

239
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:35,533
What's wrong?

240
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:37,567
Are you crying?

241
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:41,467
I'm asking you.

242
00:14:41,533 --> 00:14:42,633
So answer me.

243
00:14:44,367 --> 00:14:45,233
Why are you crying?

244
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:49,500
Nothing, Mom.

245
00:14:50,567 --> 00:14:51,700
Don't tell me...

246
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:56,033
you're crying because of Emma.

247
00:14:59,767 --> 00:15:01,900
She has been released
from detention.

248
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:05,967
I already granted your wish.

249
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:10,233
So you should be happy.

250
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:18,200
Emma isn't the reason
I'm crying, Mommy.

251
00:15:21,033 --> 00:15:24,467
I just can't explain
what I'm feeling.

252
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:28,267
I can't understand
my emotions.

253
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:34,267
Maybe it's because
of the medicines I'm taking.

254
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:37,633
Maybe side effects, Mommy.

255
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:44,133
This is the first time
you've told me about this.

256
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:49,300
This is the first time
I've seen you like that.

257
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:12,033
I'll give these away.

258
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:21,233
It only saddens me whenever
I see these memories.

259
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:27,433
I can't move on because of this.

260
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:33,067
You should've done
that a long time ago.

261
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:42,133
Danilo...

262
00:16:44,233 --> 00:16:45,967
I now agree
with what you want.

263
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:49,733
I'm okay with moving out.

264
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:51,533
Really? Are you sure?

265
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:54,333
I can call my boss.

266
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:56,667
I can ask for a route transfer.

267
00:16:58,667 --> 00:17:00,000
You're right, Danilo.

268
00:17:01,467 --> 00:17:04,067
I'm bringing Kayla back
to life through Mookie.

269
00:17:05,633 --> 00:17:10,133
I will always be reminded
of Mookie if we stay here.

270
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,933
We should move out.

271
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,400
I want to forget.

272
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,733
I'm tired of crying.

273
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,100
I don't want to cry anymore.

274
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:23,067
I want to be happy.

275
00:17:23,133 --> 00:17:25,100
I want to be happy.

276
00:17:26,133 --> 00:17:28,067
I don't want this anymore.

277
00:17:28,133 --> 00:17:31,633
I want to be happy.

278
00:17:35,533 --> 00:17:36,400
I don't want this anymore.

279
00:17:36,467 --> 00:17:38,500
It's so hard.

280
00:17:39,567 --> 00:17:42,100
I'm tired of being sad.

281
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:51,200
Mommy Emma, why did you come
back only to leave me again?

282
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:54,167
Why do you have to say goodbye?

283
00:17:55,233 --> 00:17:58,300
It's so painful that
I won't see you anymore.

284
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:02,933
You're the best person
I've met in my entire life.

285
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:07,900
Sometimes, I wish you
were my mother.

286
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:11,433
Because I experienced loving
without fear only with you.

287
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:14,533
I will miss you so much.

288
00:18:15,533 --> 00:18:17,067
I love you so much.

289
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:26,400
Here's your juice, Ma'am.

290
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:28,467
Here.

291
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:30,533
Excuse me.

292
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:32,667
Flor?

293
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:37,233
Ma'am?

294
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:39,400
What's going
on with Mookie?

295
00:18:40,167 --> 00:18:41,067
Why, Ma'am?

296
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:44,367
I don't notice anything
strange about her.

297
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:48,367
She was down when
I came to see her.

298
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,400
She also didn't
want to eat.

299
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:54,233
She said she doesn't
have the appetite.

300
00:18:56,167 --> 00:18:58,667
Mookie's often like that.

301
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:01,667
Maybe she just
doesn't feel well.

302
00:19:03,667 --> 00:19:05,967
She wasn't like
that before I left.

303
00:19:08,033 --> 00:19:10,367
I also saw her crying.

304
00:19:14,433 --> 00:19:16,333
Did something happen
while I was away?

305
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,100
What are you
hiding from me?

306
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:24,200
Ma'am, I swear, I'm not
hiding anything from you.

307
00:19:25,467 --> 00:19:26,533
Well, that's good...

308
00:19:28,567 --> 00:19:30,933
if you want to keep your job.

309
00:19:31,467 --> 00:19:32,400
Yes, Ma'am.

310
00:19:32,467 --> 00:19:34,633
Please excuse me.

311
00:19:43,067 --> 00:19:45,400
What are you keeping
from me, Mookie?

312
00:19:58,533 --> 00:20:01,200
Obet's annoying.

313
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:04,233
He didn't bring
the pail inside.

314
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:08,233
Oh, no!

315
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:09,667
I forgot I was cooking!

316
00:20:09,733 --> 00:20:11,033
Mookie!

317
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:11,900
Stay there.

318
00:20:11,967 --> 00:20:13,233
I'll just check on
what I'm cooking.

319
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:14,333
You can eat after.

320
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:15,333
I'll be right back.

321
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:16,467
- Stay there.
- Okay, Flor.

322
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:17,367
Okay.

323
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:24,000
Mookie?

324
00:21:26,467 --> 00:21:27,267
Mommy?

325
00:21:29,133 --> 00:21:30,433
What are you doing there?

326
00:21:31,333 --> 00:21:33,433
I'm just waiting for Flor.

327
00:21:35,533 --> 00:21:37,233
You can get up
on your own now?

328
00:21:39,233 --> 00:21:40,167
Since when?

329
00:21:46,333 --> 00:21:47,300
You can now walk?

330
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:51,100
Why are you
hiding it from me?

331
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:58,367
Because you insist that
this is bad for me.

332
00:21:58,433 --> 00:22:00,333
You always want me to sit down
in the wheelchair

333
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,567
or use the crutches.

334
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:05,600
What else are you
hiding from me?

335
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:14,100
Why did you hide from me
that you can already walk?

336
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:17,367
Why didn't you tell me?

337
00:22:17,433 --> 00:22:19,633
Why are you getting mad, Mommy?

338
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:23,967
Shouldn't you be happy
because I'm getting better?

339
00:22:24,667 --> 00:22:26,067
Because you kept it from me.

340
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,067
Why didn't you tell me?

341
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:31,400
Is it because you're
planning to escape?

342
00:22:32,433 --> 00:22:34,600
Do you want to go to Emma?

343
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:35,467
Is that what you want?

344
00:22:36,533 --> 00:22:38,200
If only I could.

345
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:43,267
But she said goodbye
to me because of you.

346
00:22:44,367 --> 00:22:45,233
So, it's true.

347
00:22:47,167 --> 00:22:50,000
You and Emma met at my house!

348
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:54,367
And now you're blaming me?

349
00:22:56,300 --> 00:22:57,567
This is my house!

350
00:22:58,067 --> 00:22:59,700
- I own you...
- Mommy, you're hurting me.

351
00:22:59,767 --> 00:23:02,000
And everything
in this house!

352
00:23:02,067 --> 00:23:03,467
Mommy, you're hurting me.

353
00:23:03,533 --> 00:23:04,333
Go ahead.

354
00:23:05,333 --> 00:23:07,033
Cry for Emma!

355
00:23:08,033 --> 00:23:10,167
You're not just a liar.

356
00:23:10,233 --> 00:23:12,200
You're also ungrateful!

357
00:23:17,567 --> 00:23:21,533
I also lied for you, Mommy.

358
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:28,033
I could've reported you when
the barangay officers came.

359
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:31,733
But I didn't do it
because I respect you.

360
00:23:37,133 --> 00:23:38,267
Go inside.

361
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:44,367
I said go inside!

362
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:46,633
Go!

363
00:23:56,433 --> 00:23:57,167
Flor?

364
00:23:58,167 --> 00:23:58,667
Flor!

365
00:23:59,767 --> 00:24:00,433
Ma'am?

366
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,967
Flor, where are you?

367
00:24:03,033 --> 00:24:04,267
I'm coming, Ma'am!

368
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:05,567
What is it, Ma'am?

369
00:24:05,633 --> 00:24:07,333
Why is the gate open again?

370
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:08,233
I'm sorry, Ma'am.
Close it!

371
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:09,967
Yes, I will.

372
00:24:10,467 --> 00:24:12,000
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

373
00:24:33,733 --> 00:24:36,233
I can go out later, Flor.

374
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:37,500
Yehey!

375
00:24:37,567 --> 00:24:40,300
Today is a wonderful day.

376
00:24:40,367 --> 00:24:41,167
Amen.

377
00:24:41,233 --> 00:24:42,600
I have gotten rid of Emma.

378
00:24:42,667 --> 00:24:44,167
But Mookie's now the problem.

379
00:24:45,267 --> 00:24:47,100
She demands a lot of things.

380
00:24:47,167 --> 00:24:50,733
She's threatening me
of reporting me anytime.

381
00:24:55,833 --> 00:24:56,667
You again?

382
00:24:57,200 --> 00:25:00,000
Mommy, I'm having new meds?

383
00:25:00,067 --> 00:25:01,133
Oh, no.

384
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,333
It's the same.

385
00:25:02,433 --> 00:25:04,300
That's what you've
been taking.

386
00:25:04,367 --> 00:25:05,500
It's just another brand.

387
00:25:06,467 --> 00:25:07,467
Mookie?

388
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:09,533
Are you okay?
Why?

389
00:25:12,233 --> 00:25:12,967
Mookie?

390
00:25:13,033 --> 00:25:15,133
Mookie!
